[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=January 24, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.billboard.com%2F%23%2Fartist%2FRihanna%2Fchart-history%2F658897%3Ff%3D793%26g%3DSingles&date=2011-10-02 |archivedate=October 2, 2011 |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Gigi (musical)|The Night They Invented Champagne]]\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2011\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''Music Is Better Than Words''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Take Me Along|Nine O'Clock]]\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[I'll Be Home for Christmas]]\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2014\n| \u2014 || 28\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''Holiday for Swing''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Baby, It's Cold Outside]]\"<br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring [[Sara Bareilles]])</span>\n| \u2014 || 10\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"That Face\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2017\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|rowspan=\"3\"|''In Full Swing''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Almost Like Being in Love]]\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Have You Met Miss Jones?]]\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Half as Lovely (Twice as True)\"\n| 2019\n| \u2014 || \u2014\n| ''Once in a While''\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"font-size:90%\" | \"\u2014\" denotes a recording that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n==== As featuring artist ====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:19em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Let's Fall in Love]]\"<br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Calabria Foti featuring Seth MacFarlane)</span>\n| 2013\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|}\n\n=== Guest appearances ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of non-single guest appearances, with other performing artists, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" |Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" |Other artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Pure Imagination]]\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/barbra-streisand-to-release-encore-movie-partners-sing-broadway-album-august-26th-300282903.html|title=Barbra Streisand To Release \"ENCORE: Movie Partners Sing Broadway\" Album August 26th|date=June 10, 2016|accessdate=2 September 2016|website=[[PR Newswire]]}}</ref>\n| 2016\n| [[Barbra Streisand]]\n| ''[[Encore: Movie Partners Sing Broadway]]''\n|}\n\n== Written works ==\n* {{cite book |last=MacFarlane |first=Seth |title=A Million Ways to Die in the West |location=New York |publisher=Ballantine Books |year=2014 |isbn=978-0-553-39167-1|title-link=A Million Ways to Die in the West (novel) }}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|0532235}}\n* {{AllMusic|id=mn0000529571}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140904030339/http://www.hollywoodbowl.com/philpedia/seth-macfarlane Seth MacFarlane] on [[Hollywood Bowl]]\n\n{{Seth MacFarlane|state=expanded}}\n{{Fuzzy Door Productions}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = [[List of awards and nominations received by Seth MacFarlane|Awards for Seth MacFarlane]]\n| list  = \n{{EmmyAward VoiceOver}}\n{{EmmyAward Character Voice-Over Performance}}\n{{MTV Movie Award for Best On-Screen Duo}}\n{{2020 Television Hall of Fame}}\n}}\n\n{{Subject bar|portal1=Biography|portal2=Comedy|portal3=Animation|portal4=Television|portal6=Film |portal7=Jazz |portal8=Pop music|portal9=Connecticut| portal10=United States | commons=yes|commons-search=Category:Seth MacFarlane|q=yes|d=yes|d-search= Q188492}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Good article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Macfarlane, Seth}}\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century American singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century atheists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedian